<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-30-0370 </DOCNO><TEXT>The roentgen diagnosis of tumors of the spinal cord and its coveringsand herniation of intervertebral discs are considered in this chapter,which includes brief references to the findings in certain inflammatorylesions and vascular malformations. Roentgen examination for the detectionof these conditions are discussed under four main headings: (1) plainroentgenograms of the spine without the use of contrast media, (2) myelography,or contrast examination, of the spinal canal, (3) computerized tomographic(CT) scanning both with and without contrast medium, and (4) magneticresonance (MR) imaging.</TEXT></DOC>